race.description: Celebrating The Life Of Ray Oliver Maiden
race.comment: LONGTIMEBELIEVER (6) has been runner-up off a couple of bad draws at Narrogin this season, and is closer to the fence for her peak run. She will find this company no harder, and she is poised to go one better. On top. PARIAH'S THANKS (10) was a beaten favourite on debut at Bunbury at the end of last season, and will resume at an easier level. She won the latest of her 2 tune-up Lark trials, and she can take this out, especially after a 2kg claim. LOVIN' ON ME (7) showed pace to lead fresh up in her first run for the local Paul Hunter stable. She has the pole position and will again take some pegging back. REGGIO CALABRIA (1) has raced his way into some decent form this season after joining the Roy Rogers stable. He fought hard when finishing third here 9 days ago, and he is definitely worth including in all combinations. DANCING SPIRIT (11) makes her debut from the Adam Durrant stable, and William Pike has the ride. That is a winning combination, so don't risk her.
